1: <sup>1</sup> Praise ye the LORD. Praise, O ye servants of the LORD, praise the name of the LORD.
2: <sup>2</sup> Blessed be the name of the LORD from this time forth and for evermore.
3: <sup>3</sup> From the rising of the sun unto the going down of the same the LORD’s name is to be praised.
4: <sup>4</sup> The LORD is high above all nations, and his glory above the heavens.
5: <sup>5</sup> Who is like unto the LORD our God, who dwelleth on high,
6: <sup>6</sup> Who humbleth himself to behold the things that are in heaven, and in the earth!
7: <sup>7</sup> He raiseth up the poor out of the dust, and lifteth the needy out of the dunghill;
8: <sup>8</sup> That he may set him with princes, even with the princes of his people.
9: <sup>9</sup> He maketh the barren woman to keep house, and to be a joyful mother of children. Praise ye the LORD.
